WEBVTT

00:08.041 --> 00:10.041
[ominous music playing]

00:54.250 --> 00:56.250
[ominous music intensifies]

01:29.333 --> 01:32.707
[man on comm] <i>Good copy, Sapper Patrol.
You're exiting the green zone now.</i>

01:32.708 --> 01:35.624
<i>10th Mountain's convoy
is stranded, no sitrep.</i>

01:35.625 --> 01:38.415
<i>Be advised,
Spartans convoy is in a black spot.</i>

01:38.416 --> 01:40.790
<i>Comms will be sketchy.
Stay sharp, watch your six.</i>

01:40.791 --> 01:41.791
[comm chirps]

01:45.083 --> 01:47.083
[ominous music continues]

01:49.541 --> 01:51.541
[soldiers chattering indistinctly]

02:03.916 --> 02:05.916
[music fades]

02:07.750 --> 02:11.000
Who's the full-fledged moron
responsible for this clusterfuck?

02:13.625 --> 02:15.915
Who's the meathead calling me a moron?

02:15.916 --> 02:18.499
Meathead? You fucked up my morning pass.

02:18.500 --> 02:21.083
- Oh, what are you gonna do about it?
- What am I gonna do?

02:22.000 --> 02:24.457
Noogie, baby! Got you again.

02:24.458 --> 02:26.707
[both laughing]

02:26.708 --> 02:29.875
- Wait, you know this guy?
- This one? Nah, never met him.

02:30.625 --> 02:33.458
I just have the exact same tattoo
by coincidence.

02:35.916 --> 02:37.165
Really?

02:37.166 --> 02:39.125
He's my big brother, numbnuts.

02:39.625 --> 02:41.625
- Good to see you, bro.
- You too.

02:42.416 --> 02:43.540
[older brother grunts]

02:43.541 --> 02:45.125
[jets roaring overhead]

02:46.250 --> 02:48.374
- What'd this idiot do?
- I don't know.

02:48.375 --> 02:50.875
Hey, Tommy, a bit of hospitality.
Get the shit.

02:52.958 --> 02:55.540
[brother] Let me give you a science lesson
on the laws of physics.

02:55.541 --> 02:57.916
Walk you through
what you should have learned in 8th grade.

02:58.500 --> 03:00.624
First law of thermodynamics.

03:00.625 --> 03:03.708
Energy can't be created or destroyed,
so it's gotta go somewhere.

03:04.375 --> 03:07.790
When you idiots fill these trucks
with Stop Leak, you block the vents.

03:07.791 --> 03:11.249
Heat can't escape.
Pressure builds till the radiator blows.

03:11.250 --> 03:12.416
You listening to this, Tommy?

03:14.541 --> 03:16.082
[softly] Get that shit out of here.

03:16.083 --> 03:17.790
I know it was you.

03:17.791 --> 03:19.750
Mechanics keep ratting you out.

03:21.666 --> 03:23.415
Why do you do it?

03:23.416 --> 03:25.582
- You just don't care?
- No, I care.

03:25.583 --> 03:27.540
Sure, I care about this fucking golf cart

03:27.541 --> 03:30.207
I get to drive around the desert
breaking down every five minutes.

03:30.208 --> 03:32.999
- Your fault.
- Man, we should be on the front lines.

03:33.000 --> 03:35.250
Fucking kicking doors
like we said when we joined.

03:35.916 --> 03:37.749
You know, we were all,
"Don't fucking quit."

03:37.750 --> 03:39.249
What'd we do? We fucking quit.

03:39.250 --> 03:40.625
Dude, what are you talking about?

03:41.208 --> 03:45.874
I'm talking about
Ranger Assessment Selection Program.

03:45.875 --> 03:47.499
[poignant music playing]

03:47.500 --> 03:48.665
My God.

03:48.666 --> 03:50.499
- RASP?
- [younger brother] Yeah.

03:50.500 --> 03:51.583
Dude, take Tommy.

03:52.791 --> 03:54.416
Tommy? He can't even spell "Ranger."

03:55.166 --> 03:56.790
Intake starts in June.

03:56.791 --> 03:58.375
That ship has sailed.

04:00.333 --> 04:02.333
Rangers are fucking hardcore.

04:02.833 --> 04:04.040
I'm fucking old.

04:04.041 --> 04:06.707
- You're fucking ugly.
- No, I checked the cutoff. We're good.

04:06.708 --> 04:09.457
Bro, you wanna be a Ranger,
go be a Ranger.

04:09.458 --> 04:10.708
You don't need my permission.

04:12.583 --> 04:14.750
I wanted to do it together, you know?

04:15.250 --> 04:17.000
Like we promised each other.

04:18.083 --> 04:20.000
Bro, we were 18.

04:21.125 --> 04:23.165
We also said
we were gonna start a thrash band.

04:23.166 --> 04:25.499
Come on, man, just imagine.

04:25.500 --> 04:29.040
You and me, getting our Ranger Scrolls.

04:29.041 --> 04:31.624
Fucking running across the tarmac.
Black Hawks.

04:31.625 --> 04:33.541
First boots on the ground.

04:35.916 --> 04:36.958
[chuckles]

04:38.958 --> 04:42.000
- That does sound pretty awesome.
- Yeah.

04:43.166 --> 04:44.666
[laughs]

04:46.041 --> 04:48.333
All right. You're in, I'm in.

04:49.291 --> 04:50.125
You promise?

04:51.541 --> 04:52.541
Always.

04:55.791 --> 04:57.041
Unbelievable.

04:58.000 --> 05:00.874
- I just gotta top it off with coolant.
- I got that shit.

05:00.875 --> 05:03.083
- Are you sure?
- Yeah, get outta here!

05:04.791 --> 05:07.791
[groans] I don't see you
screwing this up at all.

05:08.541 --> 05:10.624
Hey, Tom, fill it up.

05:10.625 --> 05:14.332
- We're both gonna be badass Army Rangers!
- Starting to regret saying yes already.

05:14.333 --> 05:15.999
- Tier one, baby!
- [laughs]

05:16.000 --> 05:17.749
Hey, you're not gonna say goodbye?

05:17.750 --> 05:20.457
I'll see you tomorrow
when you fill it up again with Stop Leak.

05:20.458 --> 05:22.249
We're gonna be Rangers, baby!

05:22.250 --> 05:23.875
[soldier 1] Incoming!

05:24.458 --> 05:26.082
- [dramatic music playing]
- [yells]

05:26.083 --> 05:28.082
- [soldier 2] Contact!
- [machine guns firing]

05:28.083 --> 05:29.500
Mortar incoming!

05:31.750 --> 05:33.125
Get down!

05:36.166 --> 05:39.166
[soldier 3] Go! Get up!

05:42.291 --> 05:44.291
[sound fades]

05:47.000 --> 05:49.958
- [unsettling music playing]
- [high-pitched ringing]

05:56.375 --> 05:59.416
[muffled screams]

06:04.833 --> 06:06.125
[unsettling music continues]

06:23.000 --> 06:24.583
[yells]

06:26.291 --> 06:27.333
[gasping]

06:29.750 --> 06:31.790
- [gasps]
- [music fades]

06:31.791 --> 06:33.791
[breathing heavily]

06:39.958 --> 06:41.958
[wistful music playing]

06:49.833 --> 06:51.374
[music turns ominous]

06:51.375 --> 06:52.749
[cadre 1] Five minutes to base.

06:52.750 --> 06:54.708
Get your packs ready!

07:11.833 --> 07:13.833
[music turns dramatic]

07:21.958 --> 07:25.499
[cadre 2] Welcome to
the Ranger Assessment Selection Program!

07:25.500 --> 07:31.624
All candidates must proceed at pace
to the induction hall immediately!

07:31.625 --> 07:32.540
[cadre 3] Move!

07:32.541 --> 07:34.290
[cadre 2] You will receive a Ziploc bag.

07:34.291 --> 07:37.874
Place your name, paper,
and rank inside that Ziploc bag.

07:37.875 --> 07:40.707
- Anything personal, hand it over.
- [cadre 3] Tuck in your shirt!

07:40.708 --> 07:42.749
[cadre 2] Jewelry, phones, wallets, meds.

07:42.750 --> 07:44.582
You no longer have a name.

07:44.583 --> 07:45.790
You are a number!

07:45.791 --> 07:47.415
You are now number 44.

07:47.416 --> 07:48.375
Next!

07:49.166 --> 07:52.207
- You are now number 198.
- [cadres yelling indistinctly]

07:52.208 --> 07:54.249
- [cadre 4] 190.
- [soldier] Yes, sir.

07:54.250 --> 07:56.832
As an E-6, you'll be assigned team leader.

07:56.833 --> 07:59.165
- State your consent.
- Yes, Sergeant.

07:59.166 --> 08:00.500
You're now number 7.

08:01.250 --> 08:02.957
[cadre 4] Look who's back.

08:02.958 --> 08:05.665
- One strike and you'll be out again.
- If I may say so, Sergeant--

08:05.666 --> 08:07.000
- Shut the fuck up.
- Yeah.

08:07.583 --> 08:10.124
You are now number 15. Next!

08:10.125 --> 08:12.165
You are now number 111.

08:12.166 --> 08:13.625
[cadre 4] Number 122.

08:14.375 --> 08:17.999
Fuck me. Applied four times,
medically denied each time.

08:18.000 --> 08:19.999
But he just made the age cutoff.

08:20.000 --> 08:21.375
You got a plan B?

08:22.458 --> 08:23.540
No, Sergeant.

08:23.541 --> 08:25.249
[dramatic music playing]

08:25.250 --> 08:28.124
As an E-6,
you will be assigned team leader.

08:28.125 --> 08:29.499
State your consent.

08:29.500 --> 08:30.500
I'd rather not.

08:32.250 --> 08:34.333
[cadre 2] Ten minutes to formation!

08:35.916 --> 08:37.041
You are now number 81.

08:38.125 --> 08:40.249
- Yes, Sergeant.
- [cadre 2] Ten minutes to formation!

08:40.250 --> 08:43.665
Rangers are the spearhead
of the United States Army.

08:43.666 --> 08:46.957
We are first on the ground
every single time.

08:46.958 --> 08:51.040
The fate of our nation and allies
depends on our expertise.

08:51.041 --> 08:52.249
Do you understand me?

08:52.250 --> 08:54.166
[in unison] Yes, First Sergeant!

08:54.750 --> 08:56.915
[First Sergeant]
You are about to embark on eight weeks

08:56.916 --> 08:59.665
of the hardest selection program
in the world.

08:59.666 --> 09:04.082
Whether you have been deployed in combat
or you are fresh out of basic,

09:04.083 --> 09:07.665
you can expect your emotional,
physical, and mental strength

09:07.666 --> 09:10.624
to be pushed to the absolute limit
and then some.

09:10.625 --> 09:14.499
If, by the grace of God,
you make it to the final stage,

09:14.500 --> 09:17.415
you will undertake
a 24-hour simulated mission

09:17.416 --> 09:19.457
known as Death March,

09:19.458 --> 09:22.999
completed by crossing that finish line.

09:23.000 --> 09:24.583
[dramatic music continues]

09:26.541 --> 09:32.374
At which point you will be eligible
for the Ranger Scroll, the tan beret,

09:32.375 --> 09:35.666
and the most storied regiment
in the United States Army.

09:37.125 --> 09:39.208
Attention!

09:39.708 --> 09:41.207
Rangers lead the way!

09:41.208 --> 09:42.540
[in unison] All the way!

09:42.541 --> 09:44.124
[First Sergeant] Welcome to RASP!

09:44.125 --> 09:47.665
[cadre 1] Come on, candidate!
Let's go! Let's go! Let's go!

09:47.666 --> 09:49.290
[cadre 2] Let's see what you got!

09:49.291 --> 09:51.332
Tough it out! Let's go!

09:51.333 --> 09:54.082
[First Sergeant]
<i>We are looking for elite warriors!</i>

09:54.083 --> 09:56.332
<i>The best of the best.</i>

09:56.333 --> 09:58.749
[cadre 3] Seventeen,
get the fuck out of here!

09:58.750 --> 10:01.915
[First Sergeant] <i>Every week,
those who fail will be eliminated.</i>

10:01.916 --> 10:03.415
[cadre 4] We just fucking started!

10:03.416 --> 10:07.749
[First Sergeant]
16, 27, 29, 53, step forward.

10:07.750 --> 10:10.624
- Pack your bags. You are non-selects.
- [cadre 5] Get out.

10:10.625 --> 10:12.499
- [cadre 6] Come on, 81!
- [soldiers] 38.

10:12.500 --> 10:13.333
[cadre 6] Down!

10:14.083 --> 10:15.082
Up!

10:15.083 --> 10:16.999
- [soldiers] Thirty-nine!
- [cadre 6] Down!

10:17.000 --> 10:17.915
[soldiers] Forty!

10:17.916 --> 10:20.749
[First Sergeant] If you're thinking
about quitting, do it now.

10:20.750 --> 10:22.541
[dramatic music continues]

10:25.958 --> 10:27.665
<i>- Welcome to week three.</i>
- [grunts]

10:27.666 --> 10:29.457
[First Sergeant] <i>The culling of the herd.</i>

10:29.458 --> 10:31.624
This one's broken, get him out of here!

10:31.625 --> 10:32.874
[cadre 2] Pick up those feet!

10:32.875 --> 10:34.915
[First Sergeant]
<i>There's no shame in quitting.</i>

10:34.916 --> 10:36.582
<i>Most of you will quit.</i>

10:36.583 --> 10:38.957
[cadre 6] Do you really
have what it takes?

10:38.958 --> 10:40.208
Rangers lead the way!

10:41.791 --> 10:47.082
[First Sergeant]
77, 84, 142, step forward.

10:47.083 --> 10:49.207
You are non-selects. Pack your bags.

10:49.208 --> 10:51.583
[dramatic music continues]

10:53.750 --> 10:56.374
[cadre 4 over bullhorn]
Four weeks down! Four weeks to go!

10:56.375 --> 10:57.707
You made it halfway.

10:57.708 --> 11:01.791
But if you think it gets any easier,
you are wrong!

11:05.416 --> 11:09.082
I'm just saying, once we join regiment,
it's top-secret clearance, right?

11:09.083 --> 11:11.624
Means they're gonna have to
tell us the truth about some things.

11:11.625 --> 11:15.832
Y'all know what I'm talking about.
I'm talking Area 51, moon landings.

11:15.833 --> 11:18.040
I'm talking Tupac. Come on.

11:18.041 --> 11:19.415
You're talking shit.

11:19.416 --> 11:23.041
You think they're just gonna hand over
an envelope of secrets with your scroll?

11:23.625 --> 11:25.915
- [15] Hell yeah.
- [44] That's not how it works, bro.

11:25.916 --> 11:28.165
[15] Oh, and how would you know that, 44?

11:28.166 --> 11:30.415
I was DOD. I had the clearance.

11:30.416 --> 11:33.707
Real question is why they gave us
rifles with blanks in them

11:33.708 --> 11:36.165
when you can bet
there's some good hunting up here.

11:36.166 --> 11:37.290
Yeah.

11:37.291 --> 11:39.082
'Cause otherwise we'd all shoot 15.

11:39.083 --> 11:41.124
[laughing]

11:41.125 --> 11:42.290
[15] Very funny, 7.

11:42.291 --> 11:43.250
[cadre 1] Look out.

11:44.250 --> 11:45.500
[cadre 4] Here comes the first.

11:46.916 --> 11:48.707
[cadre 1]
Where's everyone else, candidate?

11:48.708 --> 11:50.125
Behind me, Sarge.

11:52.208 --> 11:53.208
[stopwatch beeps]

11:56.791 --> 11:58.165
[15] Hey, slow down, Superman.

11:58.166 --> 12:00.166
Making the rest of us look bad.

12:01.625 --> 12:04.250
[indistinct chatter and laughter]

12:09.958 --> 12:12.958
- [dramatic music playing]
- [soldiers yelling and cheering]

12:17.458 --> 12:18.832
[cheering and whistling]

12:18.833 --> 12:20.000
[grunting]

12:21.208 --> 12:22.582
[whistle blows]

12:22.583 --> 12:25.082
[cadre 4] That is exactly
what I was talking about.

12:25.083 --> 12:27.457
[cadre 2] Now, we got a lot
of hopped-up 11 Bravos

12:27.458 --> 12:28.957
who know how to shoot a rifle,

12:28.958 --> 12:32.624
but I want a show of hands
who's actually been deployed.

12:32.625 --> 12:34.916
Where'd you serve, 109?

12:35.416 --> 12:38.165
Fort Benning, Sergeant.
Basic, AIT, and airborne.

12:38.166 --> 12:39.374
Honor grad. Top of the class.

12:39.375 --> 12:42.374
Deployments, candidate,
not potty training.

12:42.375 --> 12:44.040
And what about you, 60?

12:44.041 --> 12:46.374
19-Kilo, M1 Abrams crewman, Sergeant.

12:46.375 --> 12:48.290
Hot damn, a tanker.

12:48.291 --> 12:51.665
- Maybe you can valet my Lambo.
- [soldiers laugh]

12:51.666 --> 12:52.874
What about you, 81?

12:52.875 --> 12:56.582
12 Bravo, combat engineer, 213th CSSB.

12:56.583 --> 12:58.540
Who were you supporting, Sapper?

12:58.541 --> 12:59.625
Third Brigade.

13:00.333 --> 13:01.750
10th Mountain Division.

13:02.458 --> 13:03.415
Spartans.

13:03.416 --> 13:05.249
[soldiers whisper indistinctly]

13:05.250 --> 13:07.500
[dramatic music continues]

13:09.916 --> 13:11.083
All right.

13:14.000 --> 13:15.416
Let's see what you got.

13:17.083 --> 13:18.375
[cadre 7] Ready! Up!

13:19.666 --> 13:21.125
Ready! Up!

13:25.166 --> 13:28.457
- What happened to him?
- 213th was helping a stranded convoy.

13:28.458 --> 13:30.958
Taliban showed up
and smoked the whole unit.

13:31.458 --> 13:32.999
[60] Holy shit.

13:33.000 --> 13:34.665
That's him.

13:34.666 --> 13:37.125
- I heard he got a Silver Star.
- What?

13:37.958 --> 13:38.957
No shit.

13:38.958 --> 13:42.040
[woman on TV] <i>NASA has detected
a massive interstellar object</i>

13:42.041 --> 13:44.832
<i>believed to originate
from outside our solar system,</i>

13:44.833 --> 13:46.415
<i>projected to pass by Earth…</i>

13:46.416 --> 13:48.832
You probably think
NASA's making that shit up too.

13:48.833 --> 13:50.957
<i>Although it'll transit
close to Earth's orbit,</i>

13:50.958 --> 13:53.207
<i>officials say there is no cause for alarm.</i>

13:53.208 --> 13:54.166
Yeah.

13:54.791 --> 13:56.333
[tense music playing]

13:57.000 --> 14:02.207
146, 148, 149, step forward!

14:02.208 --> 14:04.625
Pack your bags. You are non-selects.

14:08.083 --> 14:11.249
You're telling me that guy
won a Silver fucking Star?

14:11.250 --> 14:12.250
That's what I heard.

14:13.166 --> 14:16.124
They say the only survivor carried
his brother ten miles back to base.

14:16.125 --> 14:17.999
Wait. His actual brother?

14:18.000 --> 14:19.583
That's what they said.

14:20.708 --> 14:22.083
Hey, 81.

14:22.666 --> 14:25.625
- Is it true what happened in Kandahar?
- [7] Fifteen.

14:26.208 --> 14:29.125
- Mind your business, man.
- I just wanna know if he's a hero or not.

14:30.000 --> 14:32.290
Who the fuck is talking in the DFAC?

14:32.291 --> 14:34.332
Don't tell me that was you, 15.

14:34.333 --> 14:36.166
You looking to recycle again?

14:37.958 --> 14:39.041
It was me, Sergeant.

14:40.083 --> 14:40.999
[sergeant] Bullshit!

14:41.000 --> 14:42.457
Extra hill climb!

14:42.458 --> 14:44.624
Everyone, thank 15!

14:44.625 --> 14:45.708
[soldiers groan]

14:49.291 --> 14:51.540
Forty-four, why are you here?

14:51.541 --> 14:53.290
To fight with the best!

14:53.291 --> 14:54.832
[cadre 1] Sixty, why are you here?

14:54.833 --> 14:56.499
To serve in an elite unit!

14:56.500 --> 14:58.666
Eighty-one, why are you here?

14:59.250 --> 15:00.875
To cross that finish line.

15:02.708 --> 15:05.415
[First Sergeant]
<i>This is not just a physical test.</i>

15:05.416 --> 15:08.374
<i>This is a mental and emotional test.</i>

15:08.375 --> 15:11.124
<i>If you cannot control what's inside,</i>

15:11.125 --> 15:13.832
<i>you will not control what's outside.</i>

15:13.833 --> 15:15.833
[poignant, pensive music playing]

15:28.916 --> 15:31.415
- [soldiers grunting]
- [whistle blows]

15:31.416 --> 15:33.124
[cadre 2] Thirty-second break!

15:33.125 --> 15:35.125
- [soldiers gasping]
- [music fades]

15:42.416 --> 15:44.416
[dramatic music playing]

15:46.166 --> 15:47.124
[gasps]

15:47.125 --> 15:48.457
[7] D.F.Q.?

15:48.458 --> 15:50.291
Don't Fucking Quit, right?

15:52.083 --> 15:53.415
How'd you know that?

15:53.416 --> 15:55.540
[whistle blows]

15:55.541 --> 15:56.416
Lucky guess.

15:57.083 --> 16:00.165
[cadre 2] All right, people,
we are back! Let's go! Let's go!

16:00.166 --> 16:02.499
Come on, candidates! This ain't recess.

16:02.500 --> 16:05.166
Come on, 15, move it out! Let's go!

16:07.250 --> 16:08.749
[cadre 8] Breach! Breach! Breach!

16:08.750 --> 16:10.290
[dramatic music playing]

16:10.291 --> 16:11.291
[81] Clear!

16:11.875 --> 16:15.915
This is week six! You'll be abseiling
on a figure-eight device!

16:15.916 --> 16:18.291
This shit will save your life.

16:19.875 --> 16:23.749
[First Sergeant]
65, 48, and 143, step forward!

16:23.750 --> 16:25.625
Pack your bags, you are non-selects!

16:28.458 --> 16:30.041
[soldier 1] Come on! Cover me!

16:30.875 --> 16:32.374
Move! Move! Move!

16:32.375 --> 16:33.291
[soldier 2] Move it!

16:33.875 --> 16:34.915
[soldier 1] Covering!

16:34.916 --> 16:35.999
Run!

16:36.000 --> 16:37.832
[soldier 1] Move it! Quick!

16:37.833 --> 16:39.083
Move! Move! Move!

16:40.416 --> 16:42.458
[Spartan soldier] <i>Incoming!</i>

16:44.416 --> 16:45.332
[gasps]

16:45.333 --> 16:47.415
[breathing heavily]

16:47.416 --> 16:49.499
[unsettling music playing]

16:49.500 --> 16:50.583
[door opens]

16:51.791 --> 16:54.958
Wake up, assholes!
Welcome to the final week.

16:56.708 --> 16:59.207
Yeah! Yeah! Yeah!

16:59.208 --> 17:02.208
It's a glorious day to become a Ranger.

17:03.333 --> 17:05.333
[tense music playing]

17:06.916 --> 17:09.000
[soldiers cheering and applauding]

17:19.833 --> 17:22.082
[cadre 2] Fifty-seven, out of my pool!

17:22.083 --> 17:24.790
- Fifteen, out! Forty-four, out!
- Shit!

17:24.791 --> 17:26.791
[determined music playing]

17:32.916 --> 17:33.958
I'm here!

17:34.791 --> 17:37.750
- All right. Stay with me!
- [emotional music playing]

17:40.083 --> 17:42.500
Stay with me. Please.

17:53.083 --> 17:54.333
Hang in there!

17:57.500 --> 17:59.500
[groaning]

18:07.958 --> 18:11.208
Stay with me. I got you. Breathe!

18:15.833 --> 18:18.625
[yelling]

18:30.750 --> 18:32.750
- [cadres grunt]
- [music fades]

18:33.708 --> 18:36.166
[cadre 9] Jeez. [grunting]

18:42.125 --> 18:43.540
[cadre 9 grunting]

18:43.541 --> 18:46.624
- [sighs]
- [coughing]

18:46.625 --> 18:49.333
Sapper, you are officially
one crazy motherfucker.

18:53.625 --> 18:55.915
[Sergeant Major] He's a liability.

18:55.916 --> 18:58.207
I want to see him in my office.

18:58.208 --> 19:00.290
[ominous music playing]

19:00.291 --> 19:02.291
[gasping]

19:09.875 --> 19:12.290
[man on TV] <i>The asteroid
discovered last month</i>

19:12.291 --> 19:14.499
<i>continues to confound scientists</i>

19:14.500 --> 19:17.915
<i>as it now shows signs
of structural fragmentation</i>

19:17.916 --> 19:19.875
<i>with uniform sections splitting apart.</i>

19:20.583 --> 19:24.624
<i>Some experts believe
it may not be a single object at all,</i>

19:24.625 --> 19:28.374
<i>but rather a cluster
of smaller interstellar bodies…</i>

19:28.375 --> 19:30.375
[ominous music intensifies]

19:31.458 --> 19:33.874
- [music stops]
- [First Sergeant] Come on in, candidate.

19:33.875 --> 19:36.041
<i>The situation is being closely monitored.</i>

19:37.916 --> 19:41.499
Unfortunately, First Sergeant Torres and I
are going to recommend

19:41.500 --> 19:44.833
that you retire from the course,
effective immediately.

19:45.416 --> 19:46.415
You're done.

19:46.416 --> 19:47.790
- I'm done?
- [Torres] Sit down.

19:47.791 --> 19:50.541
- On what grounds?!
- Sit down, soldier!

19:53.291 --> 19:55.415
Sergeant Major,
I haven't failed an event yet.

19:55.416 --> 19:58.082
Your physical strength is not in question.

19:58.083 --> 20:01.000
What concerns us
is what's going on inside your head.

20:02.333 --> 20:04.665
Cadre says you're not sleeping.

20:04.666 --> 20:07.749
Peer review indicates you're not bonding
with the other candidates.

20:07.750 --> 20:09.415
And I've known since day one

20:09.416 --> 20:11.958
you've ducked every single opportunity
to be a team leader.

20:12.583 --> 20:14.874
These aren't the hallmarks
of a stable candidate.

20:14.875 --> 20:16.332
[Sergeant Major] No, they're not.

20:16.333 --> 20:21.083
Usually, when a soldier goes
through a world of shit like you have,

20:21.666 --> 20:24.832
they take a little time off, recuperate,

20:24.833 --> 20:31.125
maybe attend at least one of those
VA-recommended group therapy sessions.

20:33.958 --> 20:35.416
But you didn't do that.

20:36.708 --> 20:41.290
What your record says is that
the very morning of your discharge,

20:41.291 --> 20:43.457
you applied for RASP.

20:43.458 --> 20:44.832
And, in fact, since then,

20:44.833 --> 20:50.250
repeatedly applying for RASP
seems to be the only thing you've done.

20:51.500 --> 20:53.000
Now, why is that?

20:55.125 --> 20:58.166
I just want to get across
that finish line, Sergeant Major.

21:01.208 --> 21:04.458
That finish line is a starting line.

21:08.250 --> 21:09.333
[Sergeant Major] Son,

21:09.916 --> 21:11.916
I'm gonna be honest with you.

21:13.666 --> 21:17.040
You're one of the most promising
candidates we've ever seen.

21:17.041 --> 21:20.916
And Sergeant Torres and I
think you have a lot of potential.

21:21.750 --> 21:26.791
Truth is, we could kick you out
right here, right now.

21:28.208 --> 21:30.291
But there'd be no coming back.

21:31.125 --> 21:32.125
So, instead,

21:33.375 --> 21:34.499
what I have here

21:34.500 --> 21:36.958
is a voluntary quit slip.

21:37.875 --> 21:41.665
Now, I want you to do yourself a favor
and sign it.

21:41.666 --> 21:43.999
[somber music playing]

21:44.000 --> 21:45.874
You're an engineer.

21:45.875 --> 21:48.790
So you know
even the most powerful machines

21:48.791 --> 21:50.291
have their limits.

21:52.041 --> 21:54.583
And I think you've reached yours.

22:10.375 --> 22:11.875
If you don't mind…

22:15.750 --> 22:17.916
I'd like to go prep for parade now.

22:19.666 --> 22:21.666
[music fades]

22:22.666 --> 22:25.291
You get the fuck out of my office.

22:26.500 --> 22:27.416
[door opens]

22:29.000 --> 22:30.000
[door closes]

22:36.333 --> 22:38.332
How do you want to play this?

22:38.333 --> 22:40.333
[ominous music playing]

22:42.916 --> 22:46.958
[Torres] 38, 44, 57,

22:47.958 --> 22:49.000
Sixty,

22:49.500 --> 22:51.457
Eighty-one,

22:51.458 --> 22:56.958
96, 109, 111, step forward.

22:59.875 --> 23:02.749
I'm sorry to say that those of you
who did not step forward,

23:02.750 --> 23:05.374
pack your bags, you are non-selects.

23:05.375 --> 23:07.375
[dramatic music playing]

23:10.750 --> 23:12.790
To those who stepped forward, congratulations.

23:12.791 --> 23:14.415
You made it through to the final round.

23:14.416 --> 23:17.707
You have 30 minutes to gear up
and get ready for one final test

23:17.708 --> 23:20.457
to see if you have what it takes
to be a Ranger.

23:20.458 --> 23:23.374
- You are dismissed.
- Mama-say mama-sa, motherfucker!

23:23.375 --> 23:24.374
Let's go!

23:24.375 --> 23:25.832
[both yell]

23:25.833 --> 23:26.915
[60] Let's go!

23:26.916 --> 23:28.208
[whooping and cheering]

23:30.125 --> 23:33.708
[music crescendos, then fades]

23:34.500 --> 23:36.625
[Torres] All right, listen up.
Here's the situation.

23:37.208 --> 23:40.707
Got a classified aircraft
shot down behind enemy lines.

23:40.708 --> 23:43.457
Rangers are tasked with recon and rescue.

23:43.458 --> 23:47.624
Two Black Hawks are gonna carry you down
to your drop zone deep in enemy territory.

23:47.625 --> 23:50.665
You'll then maneuver
toward the downed aircraft's position.

23:50.666 --> 23:54.499
You need to destroy the aircraft
so it doesn't fall into enemy hands.

23:54.500 --> 23:56.083
But we'll provide you extra C4.

23:56.916 --> 24:01.499
Next, locate the rebel village outpost
where the pilot of the downed aircraft

24:01.500 --> 24:03.290
is being held as a POW.

24:03.291 --> 24:08.082
You can expect perimeter surveillance
and 360 security.

24:08.083 --> 24:11.749
Your rifles have blank-firing adapters,
so you can't shoot.

24:11.750 --> 24:15.165
But be warned,
you may be ambushed by cadre at any time.

24:15.166 --> 24:17.540
Your squad will be equipped
with a single VHF

24:17.541 --> 24:19.749
to provide round-the-clock sitreps.

24:19.750 --> 24:21.875
Apart from that, you're on your own.

24:22.583 --> 24:23.708
Team Leader 7,

24:24.708 --> 24:26.125
you're now 2IC.

24:26.666 --> 24:28.833
And your new team leader will be

24:29.750 --> 24:30.707
Eighty-one.

24:30.708 --> 24:32.750
[dramatic music playing]

24:34.875 --> 24:37.375
Great. Mr. Finish Line.

24:37.958 --> 24:40.374
[Torres] You will bring the pilot
back to base camp

24:40.375 --> 24:42.915
and cross that finish line by 1900.

24:42.916 --> 24:46.958
If at any point during this exercise
you are successfully ambushed,

24:48.000 --> 24:50.666
the mission's over, and you have failed.

24:52.208 --> 24:54.874
[Sergeant Major]
And <i>if</i> you cross that line,

24:54.875 --> 25:01.624
I will personally award you
the US Army Ranger Regiment Scroll.

25:01.625 --> 25:03.791
Welcome to Death March.

25:04.291 --> 25:06.083
[dramatic music continues]

25:14.541 --> 25:17.000
You still think this is a good idea?

25:17.583 --> 25:21.333
He wants to be a Ranger,
he's gonna have to lead.

25:23.583 --> 25:26.250
[man on comm] <i>Ghost 1, Ghost 2,
you are cleared hot for departure.</i>

25:28.125 --> 25:31.165
- [pilot 1] <i>Ghost 1, lifting.</i>
- [pilot 2] <i>Copy. Ghost 2, lifting.</i>

25:31.166 --> 25:32.958
<i>Staying tight on your six.</i>

25:40.208 --> 25:43.958
[pilot 1] <i>Passing Angels 2.
Leveling at 150 feet AGL.</i>

25:44.791 --> 25:46.750
[pilot 2] <i>Copy. Matching altitude.</i>

25:52.875 --> 25:56.290
How much of this shit you think we rucked
in the last eight weeks?

25:56.291 --> 25:58.833
Everything except whatever that is.

26:00.125 --> 26:01.290
[loadmaster] Private quarry.

26:01.291 --> 26:04.416
You boys come across that,
you are way off course.

26:04.916 --> 26:06.916
[ominous music playing]

26:18.041 --> 26:19.875
[pilot 2 on comm] <i>Thirty seconds out.</i>

26:22.958 --> 26:25.290
We have visual on LZ.

26:25.291 --> 26:27.291
[ominous music continues]

26:31.458 --> 26:33.207
Ropes! Ropes!

26:33.208 --> 26:36.791
[loadmaster] Rope's out!
Green light! Drop! Drop! Drop!

26:45.625 --> 26:48.458
[pilot 1] <i>Chalk 1 down.
Ghost 1 up, shifting to cover.</i>

26:49.750 --> 26:51.333
Go! Go! Go!

26:55.291 --> 26:58.208
[pilot 1] <i>Half team down.
Last sticks moving.</i>

26:59.166 --> 27:00.666
[music turns dramatic]

27:02.791 --> 27:05.166
All right, let's go!

27:07.708 --> 27:09.665
[pilot 2] <i>Ghost 2 to GUC Command.</i>

27:09.666 --> 27:12.332
<i>Drop clean. Death March is in effect.</i>

27:12.333 --> 27:15.540
<i>I repeat, Death March is in effect.</i>

27:15.541 --> 27:17.541
[music fades]

27:22.083 --> 27:24.041
All right, 57. Where we at?

27:24.958 --> 27:26.875
[birds singing and chirping]

27:29.541 --> 27:33.041
Target's that direction, 20 klicks west.

27:36.750 --> 27:38.457
- [81] Okay.
- [beeps]

27:38.458 --> 27:41.249
We got exactly
23 hours, 59 minutes, and 30 seconds

27:41.250 --> 27:42.708
to get across that finish line.

27:44.666 --> 27:45.708
Any questions?

27:50.375 --> 27:52.625
Dude, that was awesome. For real.

27:53.583 --> 27:55.415
I mean, that was like
some <i>Braveheart</i> shit.

27:55.416 --> 27:56.665
That was…

27:56.666 --> 27:57.957
It was inspiring stuff.

27:57.958 --> 27:59.583
Mind if I have a word?

28:03.708 --> 28:05.916
Remember, we're all here for one reason.

28:06.708 --> 28:08.083
We never give up.

28:08.750 --> 28:11.166
I'm proud as hell to know
each and every one of y'all.

28:11.958 --> 28:12.957
Even you, 15.

28:12.958 --> 28:14.124
[scattered laughter]

28:14.125 --> 28:15.916
Let's have each other's backs out there.

28:16.500 --> 28:19.250
Let's cross that finish line
and get these scrolls together, all right?

28:20.000 --> 28:22.749
- Rangers lead the way.
- [in unison] All the way!

28:22.750 --> 28:24.041
All right.

28:25.166 --> 28:26.208
It's all you.

28:32.125 --> 28:33.374
Follow me.

28:33.375 --> 28:35.375
[ominous music playing]

28:50.958 --> 28:52.958
[gasping and grunting]

29:02.208 --> 29:03.041
[groans]

29:15.750 --> 29:19.499
Hotel-9, this is Victor-6.
We've passed phase line red. Over.

29:19.500 --> 29:20.665
[music fades]

29:20.666 --> 29:23.290
[cadre 4] <i>Roger, Victor-6.
Phase line red acquired.</i>

29:23.291 --> 29:25.916
We made some good ground.
I think the team could use a rest.

29:27.416 --> 29:30.749
But if Cadre surprises us,
they're gonna do it down by the river.

29:30.750 --> 29:34.166
We get some shut-eye now,
then we'll be primed for an ambush.

29:35.916 --> 29:37.083
Twenty minutes.

29:39.541 --> 29:41.041
All right, listen up, y'all.

29:41.583 --> 29:43.166
Twenty-minute break, no more.

29:44.458 --> 29:47.708
- Gotta be on that target by first light.
- [23] Who's on lookout?

29:48.208 --> 29:49.166
Me.

29:50.000 --> 29:52.000
[insects chittering]

29:53.166 --> 29:54.458
Hey, 81.

29:55.708 --> 29:57.458
I've been meaning to talk to you, man.

29:58.666 --> 30:00.208
Is it about the mission?

30:01.416 --> 30:04.124
Nah, it's… it's more personal. I just--

30:04.125 --> 30:05.500
Then I don't want to hear it.

30:06.000 --> 30:08.000
[poignant music playing]

30:10.750 --> 30:11.666
All right, man.

30:14.666 --> 30:15.750
All right.

30:18.000 --> 30:19.083
[7 sighs]

30:24.583 --> 30:26.583
[music turns ominous]

30:34.625 --> 30:36.583
- [deep rumbling]
- [all yell]

30:41.541 --> 30:44.207
- [soldier] Fuck this!
- Seriously, what the fuck was that?

30:44.208 --> 30:45.582
[60] Artillery fire, baby.

30:45.583 --> 30:47.874
Cadre probably clocked us sleeping.

30:47.875 --> 30:49.708
[15] So they're out there
watching us, huh?

30:50.583 --> 30:51.791
Grab your shit.

30:52.666 --> 30:53.915
We're moving out.

30:53.916 --> 30:55.916
[tense music playing]

31:03.708 --> 31:05.457
[music fades]

31:05.458 --> 31:07.458
[birds singing and chirping]

31:08.333 --> 31:09.541
You got something?

31:10.041 --> 31:11.333
[81] Midstream.

31:12.875 --> 31:14.165
Half a klick.

31:14.166 --> 31:15.666
[tense, pensive music playing]

31:19.041 --> 31:21.874
[7] Cadre really went all-in
with the special effects.

31:21.875 --> 31:23.749
Sure looks classified.

31:23.750 --> 31:26.457
I think they're gonna try
to smoke us upriver.

31:26.458 --> 31:27.500
Yeah.

31:28.666 --> 31:29.749
No doubt.

31:29.750 --> 31:32.624
111, call in our sitrep.

31:32.625 --> 31:36.000
Hotel-9, this is Victor-6.
We're near target. Over.

31:36.500 --> 31:37.915
[81] Listen, here's the game plan.

31:37.916 --> 31:40.290
[111] Hotel-9, this is Victor-6.
We're near target. Over.

31:40.291 --> 31:43.333
Demo team will blow up charges
from a minimum safe distance here.

31:43.916 --> 31:46.832
The explosion will draw Cadre.
We have to be ready for a counter-ambush.

31:46.833 --> 31:48.874
You four on overwatch,
you three downstream.

31:48.875 --> 31:50.374
The rest of us take upstream.

31:50.375 --> 31:51.790
Hey, hold up.

31:51.791 --> 31:53.375
What's going on, 57?

31:54.083 --> 31:55.707
According to briefing coordinates,

31:55.708 --> 31:58.874
that target's position's off
by a few hundred meters.

31:58.875 --> 32:01.708
Might be my compass.
It's been acting up, but…

32:04.125 --> 32:06.583
Comms are down. I can't get a signal.

32:07.083 --> 32:09.249
All I got is this weird interference.

32:09.250 --> 32:11.250
[clicking and howling over comm]

32:13.333 --> 32:14.915
[15] Maybe Cadre cut comms.

32:14.916 --> 32:17.165
One last friendly "fuck you"?

32:17.166 --> 32:18.916
So what should we do?

32:19.500 --> 32:20.791
Keep your eyes open.

32:22.166 --> 32:24.375
We could be ambushed by Cadre any minute.

32:26.375 --> 32:28.375
[tense music playing]

33:11.750 --> 33:13.791
[tense music continues]

33:23.625 --> 33:26.708
[7] Come on, Cadre. Where you at?

33:29.416 --> 33:30.708
[birds squawking]

33:40.083 --> 33:41.750
[eerie music playing]

33:50.708 --> 33:53.333
Forty-four, cover me.

34:01.083 --> 34:03.375
Where the fuck is he going now?

34:05.416 --> 34:06.957
Possible Cadre.

34:06.958 --> 34:08.625
Eighty-one's gonna recon.

34:22.666 --> 34:24.625
[suspenseful music playing]

34:42.041 --> 34:43.625
Fire in the hole!

34:56.166 --> 34:57.082
What the hell?

34:57.083 --> 34:59.083
[unsettling music playing]

35:06.750 --> 35:08.333
Didn't even leave a dent.

35:10.583 --> 35:12.208
[unsettling music intensifies]

35:16.291 --> 35:18.291
[whirring]

35:34.750 --> 35:35.791
Fuck me.

35:36.958 --> 35:38.916
[music darkens]

35:51.375 --> 35:53.791
[sensors buzzing]

35:56.875 --> 35:58.291
What the hell is that?

36:05.208 --> 36:06.333
[whirring]

36:12.333 --> 36:13.457
Retreat!

36:13.458 --> 36:15.125
[grunting]

36:16.791 --> 36:18.125
[screams]

36:20.750 --> 36:22.083
- [yelling]
- [23] Sixty!

36:22.875 --> 36:24.875
- [gasping]
- [intense music playing]

36:31.333 --> 36:32.750
[whirring]

36:33.333 --> 36:35.249
- [44 grunts]
- [81 grunts]

36:35.250 --> 36:36.083
Run!

36:38.083 --> 36:40.166
[intense music continues]

36:43.375 --> 36:44.290
[yells]

36:44.291 --> 36:46.333
[grunting]

36:47.375 --> 36:48.999
[soldiers yelling]

36:49.000 --> 36:51.165
- Get out of there!
- Come on!

36:51.166 --> 36:52.375
Now! Now!

36:53.500 --> 36:55.541
[111] Oh God! Oh God, man!

36:57.541 --> 36:58.999
Whoa! Whoa! Whoa!

36:59.000 --> 37:00.457
[all gasping]

37:00.458 --> 37:02.790
[weapons firing]

37:02.791 --> 37:04.125
What the fuck is that?

37:05.625 --> 37:07.082
[clanks]

37:07.083 --> 37:08.415
[weapon trills]

37:08.416 --> 37:09.915
[81] Oh shit.

37:09.916 --> 37:10.833
Get down!

37:11.791 --> 37:13.958
[all grunting and yelling]

37:37.125 --> 37:38.041
[screams]

37:40.166 --> 37:41.208
- [yells]
- [grunts]

37:41.791 --> 37:43.874
- [groans]
- [high-pitched ringing]

37:43.875 --> 37:45.875
[dramatic music playing]

37:46.541 --> 37:48.541
[echoing gasping and groaning]

38:28.750 --> 38:31.040
[breathing raggedly]

38:31.041 --> 38:33.249
- [joints crack]
- [screams]

38:33.250 --> 38:36.416
- [109] Oh fuck! Fuck!
- [soldiers screaming and groaning]

38:37.833 --> 38:39.999
[109 screams]

38:40.000 --> 38:41.124
[23] On your feet, 96.

38:41.125 --> 38:43.500
- Shh! Shh.
- [muffled whimpers]

38:44.375 --> 38:46.874
I need you to suck it up.
Can you do that for me?

38:46.875 --> 38:47.999
[muffled] Mm-hm.

38:48.000 --> 38:49.833
[57 groans, coughs]

38:51.833 --> 38:53.082
I need your help!

38:53.083 --> 38:54.833
[23] You okay?

38:56.125 --> 38:58.207
- [44] Oh my God!
- [gasps] Ow.

38:58.208 --> 39:00.415
- [grunting]
- Hey, don't touch it. Don't touch it.

39:00.416 --> 39:02.999
I'm gonna lift you up on three, okay?

39:03.000 --> 39:04.040
One.

39:04.041 --> 39:05.790
Two, three.

39:05.791 --> 39:08.290
- [57 groaning]
- [flesh squelching]

39:08.291 --> 39:09.749
[tense music playing]

39:09.750 --> 39:11.750
[gasping and groaning]

39:13.291 --> 39:14.541
[81] Get your med kit.

39:15.041 --> 39:16.000
[soldier screaming]

39:16.583 --> 39:17.875
[81] Keep the pressure on.

39:18.375 --> 39:20.874
Fuck, it looks bad, man.
It looks really fucking bad.

39:20.875 --> 39:23.374
- Hey! Breathe.
- [57] No…

39:23.375 --> 39:24.832
[57 groaning]

39:24.833 --> 39:26.332
- We're exposed.
- I'm fucked.

39:26.333 --> 39:28.458
No, you're good. I need to move you.

39:29.375 --> 39:30.999
[57 groans]

39:31.000 --> 39:32.290
[groaning]

39:32.291 --> 39:34.582
- Fuck!
- [15] What the fuck just happened?

39:34.583 --> 39:38.499
- [81] Tourniquet his leg!
- Fifteen, the bleeding won't stop.

39:38.500 --> 39:41.207
- What the hell was that thing?
- [44] I don't know.

39:41.208 --> 39:43.665
- It was fucking shooting everybody.
- [7 groans] Motherfuck.

39:43.666 --> 39:45.082
- I'm done.
- Where's 60?

39:45.083 --> 39:48.249
He got blown in the river.
Thirteen just got frickin' smoked.

39:48.250 --> 39:51.332
- What about the demo crew?
- They're gone, man. They're fucking gone!

39:51.333 --> 39:53.332
All right, I got this. Get your gauze out.

39:53.333 --> 39:55.499
[109] Hey, don't you doze off on me, 57.

39:55.500 --> 39:56.665
[23] Stay with me.

39:56.666 --> 39:59.415
[44] Wait! Where's 72?

39:59.416 --> 40:03.416
He was next to me on the ridge.
What about 111? He has the radio.

40:04.000 --> 40:05.124
[7] Hey.

40:05.125 --> 40:06.874
We need comms. We need comms.

40:06.875 --> 40:08.708
- We need that radio.
- I'll go.

40:10.041 --> 40:12.624
[109] Hold on, 57.
Come back to the light, brother.

40:12.625 --> 40:14.082
[suspenseful music playing]

40:14.083 --> 40:15.958
[gasping]

40:28.416 --> 40:29.791
[grunts]

40:31.500 --> 40:33.500
[music turns dramatic]

40:42.583 --> 40:44.583
[tense music playing]

40:59.416 --> 41:00.250
[whispering] 111.

41:00.833 --> 41:02.125
Hey. Psst!

41:05.125 --> 41:08.125
[flames sparking]

41:09.541 --> 41:11.583
[soldier grunting and groaning]

41:16.125 --> 41:18.125
- [rumbling]
- [ominous music playing]

41:29.875 --> 41:31.875
[footsteps thudding loudly]

41:36.083 --> 41:37.208
[135] Please, no.

41:38.625 --> 41:39.790
- [whirring]
- Please.

41:39.791 --> 41:41.624
Please. No.

41:41.625 --> 41:42.916
No!

41:47.000 --> 41:48.416
[sensor buzzing]

41:51.541 --> 41:54.000
[smoke hissing]

41:59.791 --> 42:02.165
[15] Hey. Hey, keep your eyes on me.
57, look at me!

42:02.166 --> 42:04.083
- [23] You stay with us, brother.
- [15] Look at me.

42:04.625 --> 42:06.249
- That's it.
- Fifty-seven.

42:06.250 --> 42:07.415
[gasps]

42:07.416 --> 42:08.541
[15] It's all right.

42:09.875 --> 42:12.124
Fifty-seven…

42:12.125 --> 42:14.125
- [gasps softly]
- [somber music playing]

42:21.250 --> 42:22.166
He's gone.

42:32.375 --> 42:33.582
[81] We need to move!

42:33.583 --> 42:35.791
[tense music playing]

42:37.041 --> 42:39.749
- 57 is dead, man.
- And so are we if we don't move.

42:39.750 --> 42:42.624
- You find 72?
- Dead too.

42:42.625 --> 42:44.665
Hey, what about 111 and the radio?

42:44.666 --> 42:46.125
Both gone.

42:46.666 --> 42:48.165
That thing's hunting us.

42:48.166 --> 42:49.415
What the fuck is it?

42:49.416 --> 42:51.582
I don't know, but it's moving.

42:51.583 --> 42:54.207
- What do you mean it's moving?
- It's following our trail.

42:54.208 --> 42:56.582
Ditch your weapons. Grab your ropes.

42:56.583 --> 42:57.958
We need to get off this cliff.

42:58.791 --> 43:00.250
Hey! Listen to your team leader!

43:00.916 --> 43:02.750
- Let's go!
- [81] Give me your rope.

43:04.625 --> 43:06.000
I got this. Clip on.

43:11.166 --> 43:12.208
I said ditch that.

43:13.875 --> 43:14.790
[7] All right.

43:14.791 --> 43:16.125
[7 groaning]

43:18.875 --> 43:20.541
[tense music continues]

43:40.708 --> 43:42.624
Eighty-one, I'll lower 7.

43:42.625 --> 43:44.125
You spot him on the way down.

43:50.583 --> 43:52.082
Get yourself set up.

43:52.083 --> 43:53.750
- See you at the bottom.
- [7] All right.

43:57.208 --> 43:59.875
- [96] We're gonna make it, right?
- You're good. We're good, baby.

44:00.458 --> 44:02.833
Slow. There it goes. I'm going down.
You follow me, all right?

44:05.375 --> 44:06.708
[music intensifies]

44:12.000 --> 44:13.749
Come on, come on, come on.

44:13.750 --> 44:15.750
[grunting]

44:17.125 --> 44:18.166
[7] Keep going!

44:18.666 --> 44:20.166
Keep going!

44:21.083 --> 44:23.250
- [compass buzzing]
- [foreboding music playing]

44:25.791 --> 44:26.874
Hurry up!

44:26.875 --> 44:29.166
- [music intensifies]
- [footsteps thudding]

44:33.333 --> 44:34.833
Oh shit.

44:38.416 --> 44:40.249
- [thuds]
- [screaming]

44:40.250 --> 44:41.125
[81] Shh!

44:43.958 --> 44:45.582
- [gasping]
- [music fades]

44:45.583 --> 44:47.583
[sensor buzzing]

44:58.666 --> 45:00.041
[warbles]

45:01.333 --> 45:03.333
[footsteps rumbling]

45:08.708 --> 45:10.708
[footsteps echoing]

45:14.708 --> 45:17.125
[suspenseful music playing]

45:35.833 --> 45:37.541
[sensor whirring]

45:54.833 --> 45:55.999
Run!

45:56.000 --> 45:58.125
- [intense music playing]
- [grunting]

46:00.000 --> 46:00.833
[81] Run!

46:01.458 --> 46:02.916
[all yelling]

46:16.833 --> 46:18.166
Incoming!

46:20.958 --> 46:22.250
[all yelling]

46:27.833 --> 46:28.750
[109] Get up!

46:32.750 --> 46:33.790
[15] Get him!

46:33.791 --> 46:35.958
[yells]

46:38.958 --> 46:41.208
[intense music continues]

46:47.750 --> 46:49.750
[music fades]

46:51.083 --> 46:53.208
[15] Slow down. We need some rest.

46:54.625 --> 46:56.375
Eighty-one, we need to stop.

46:57.916 --> 46:59.708
Eighty-one, we need to stop!

47:01.375 --> 47:02.790
[81] All right, put him down.

47:02.791 --> 47:04.791
[all gasping and groaning]

47:08.000 --> 47:09.790
[23] It's not following us, right?

47:09.791 --> 47:10.875
[coughing]

47:12.125 --> 47:13.624
Get eyes on our six.

47:13.625 --> 47:16.125
- I need to set his leg.
- [109] Are we safe?

47:17.125 --> 47:18.958
What the actual fuck is going on?

47:19.666 --> 47:22.582
It's gotta be some R&D kinda weapons test.

47:22.583 --> 47:24.707
I think we've been set up.
We're fucking guinea pigs.

47:24.708 --> 47:25.957
[44] That is insane talk.

47:25.958 --> 47:27.832
[109] It could be the Russians
or the Chinese.

47:27.833 --> 47:30.499
[44] The Russians don't have the budget
for that kind of tech.

47:30.500 --> 47:31.999
The Chinese just copy us.

47:32.000 --> 47:33.749
- [unsettling music playing]
- [gasping]

47:33.750 --> 47:35.540
[haunting screams]

47:35.541 --> 47:37.000
[gasping]

47:38.541 --> 47:41.165
You got this. It's all good. You got it.

47:41.166 --> 47:42.790
[music turns poignant]

47:42.791 --> 47:44.166
You got it.

47:47.791 --> 47:48.874
[music fades]

47:48.875 --> 47:50.791
- Who's got morphine?
- Yeah.

47:51.375 --> 47:52.415
SKEDCO.

47:52.416 --> 47:54.125
- Copy.
- [81] Get it out.

47:55.500 --> 47:56.666
15, find me a splint.

47:57.625 --> 48:01.457
The morphine, the vials are all broken.
It must have happened in the fall.

48:01.458 --> 48:03.000
Goddamn!

48:03.958 --> 48:05.291
Just do it.

48:06.416 --> 48:07.458
Come on.

48:08.291 --> 48:09.125
Do it.

48:10.833 --> 48:12.708
- Fuck.
- [81] Okay.

48:13.750 --> 48:15.957
[7 breathing heavily]

48:15.958 --> 48:17.541
Three, two…

48:18.708 --> 48:21.291
[screaming]

48:26.291 --> 48:27.749
[109] What's happened to him?

48:27.750 --> 48:28.749
Is he dead?

48:28.750 --> 48:30.833
Blacked out from the pain. Sked.

48:31.750 --> 48:33.999
Seriously, what in God's name
was that thing?

48:34.000 --> 48:36.915
I'm telling you, brother,
this is some DARPA shit, for real.

48:36.916 --> 48:40.290
Enough with that conspiracy shit.
The DOD would never do that to us.

48:40.291 --> 48:42.249
Then why would they send us
to the exact location

48:42.250 --> 48:47.249
of a giant fucking robot with nothing
but a bunch of fucking dummy rounds?

48:47.250 --> 48:48.874
It wasn't our location.

48:48.875 --> 48:50.415
[ominous music playing]

48:50.416 --> 48:53.082
Fifty-seven was right.
Our coords were off.

48:53.083 --> 48:56.415
Whatever that thing is,
it's got some kind of magnetic field

48:56.416 --> 48:58.999
screwing with our compasses
in close proximity.

48:59.000 --> 49:00.665
My compass was flipping out too.

49:00.666 --> 49:02.624
- Where was our target then?
- [81] I saw it.

49:02.625 --> 49:03.791
An old jet.

49:04.666 --> 49:06.541
- We need to move.
- Where?

49:07.041 --> 49:08.415
[81] Village.

49:08.416 --> 49:09.915
Eight klicks west.

49:09.916 --> 49:11.999
Ditch everything
besides medical and mobility.

49:12.000 --> 49:15.749
[laughs nervously] You shitting me?
You want to cross that terrain?

49:15.750 --> 49:18.332
I hate to break it to you, man,
but look around.

49:18.333 --> 49:21.249
No more Death March,
no more RASP, there's no finish line.

49:21.250 --> 49:22.707
Yeah, no shit.

49:22.708 --> 49:24.833
No comms, no flares, no firearms.

49:25.416 --> 49:26.958
Cadre's our closest help.

49:27.750 --> 49:29.333
We carry 7 in shifts.

49:30.500 --> 49:33.041
Unless you want to sit here
and wait for him to bleed out.

49:36.375 --> 49:37.458
Help me carry him.

49:41.458 --> 49:43.458
[ominous music playing]

49:55.708 --> 49:57.125
[grunting]

50:05.083 --> 50:07.083
[music fades]

50:08.250 --> 50:10.250
It's too dangerous to cross here.

50:10.916 --> 50:12.874
Why don't we cross further down?

50:12.875 --> 50:16.125
Oh, hell no.
Those rapids get worse down there.

50:17.583 --> 50:19.666
Our best shot across is right here.

50:21.208 --> 50:23.624
[23] Hey, hold up.
How are we gonna do that?

50:23.625 --> 50:25.790
Grab your rope. We rig a zip.

50:25.791 --> 50:27.540
Four people, four ropes.

50:27.541 --> 50:29.749
Tie two together for the main line,
and pull 7 over.

50:29.750 --> 50:31.583
Shit. I don't have my rope.

50:32.666 --> 50:34.499
Ninety-six was using it.

50:34.500 --> 50:36.833
Someone's gonna have to go tandem with 7.

50:37.875 --> 50:39.040
I'll do it.

50:39.041 --> 50:41.833
- How are we gonna get the line across?
- You're not.

50:42.708 --> 50:43.708
I am.

50:44.291 --> 50:48.499
44, grab the ropes and follow me.
109, keep an eye on this.

50:48.500 --> 50:51.500
[suspenseful music playing]

51:00.583 --> 51:02.291
I'm gonna jump upstream.

51:02.875 --> 51:04.957
Current's gonna push me fast.
Keep slack in the line.

51:04.958 --> 51:07.165
It goes tight, I get sucked under.

51:07.166 --> 51:08.165
Got it?

51:08.166 --> 51:10.250
Careful, man. That shit's gonna be cold.

51:17.416 --> 51:18.291
[gasps]

51:20.500 --> 51:22.500
[grunting]

51:33.500 --> 51:35.833
[44 grunting]

51:52.333 --> 51:53.625
Come on.

51:55.708 --> 51:57.125
[music fades]

51:58.458 --> 52:00.458
[dramatic music playing]

52:01.541 --> 52:02.457
[gasps]

52:02.458 --> 52:03.375
Oh!

52:04.291 --> 52:05.250
Wait, he's out!

52:05.833 --> 52:07.416
He's out! He made it!

52:09.041 --> 52:09.875
[44] Fuck.

52:11.333 --> 52:12.291
[grunting]

52:16.250 --> 52:17.250
[15] Watch it.

52:17.916 --> 52:19.375
[suspenseful music playing]

52:23.375 --> 52:25.416
Hey, I'm gonna get you across, brother.

52:26.000 --> 52:28.083
Just hang in there. I got you.

52:39.000 --> 52:41.208
I'm ready! Eighty-one's line is secure!

52:42.208 --> 52:43.875
[23] Ready, set, pull!

52:44.375 --> 52:45.875
[both grunting]

53:03.333 --> 53:04.374
[44] Careful.

53:04.375 --> 53:05.665
[15] I'm locked on.

53:05.666 --> 53:07.165
I'm headin' across.

53:07.166 --> 53:08.749
I'm gonna go.

53:08.750 --> 53:11.458
Easy. Easy, brother. You got this, 15.

53:12.041 --> 53:14.375
- [suspenseful music continues]
- [15 grunting]

53:30.875 --> 53:32.791
[15 grunting]

53:39.500 --> 53:40.375
[grunts]

53:41.125 --> 53:42.416
[music intensifies]

53:49.083 --> 53:50.249
Fuck!

53:50.250 --> 53:51.458
He's stuck!

53:53.125 --> 53:54.916
[15 grunting]

54:10.208 --> 54:11.416
Come on!

54:12.333 --> 54:13.291
[15 gasps]

54:14.166 --> 54:15.250
[15 yells]

54:16.500 --> 54:17.582
[coughs]

54:17.583 --> 54:19.083
- [gasps]
- Shit!

54:21.625 --> 54:22.915
Pull in the slack!

54:22.916 --> 54:24.041
God! Come on. Come on.

54:30.708 --> 54:31.749
Go on.

54:31.750 --> 54:33.082
Go! Go! Go! Go!

54:33.083 --> 54:34.541
[grunting]

54:36.958 --> 54:38.458
[15 grunting]

54:39.500 --> 54:41.000
Help! Help!

54:41.958 --> 54:42.958
Fuck!

54:45.500 --> 54:46.916
[44] I'm coming!

54:49.500 --> 54:51.333
- [yelling]
- I got you!

54:53.958 --> 54:54.874
Get him up!

54:54.875 --> 54:55.915
I got him! I got him!

54:55.916 --> 54:57.083
- Move him up!
- Come on!

54:57.666 --> 54:58.832
[groans]

54:58.833 --> 55:00.832
[grunting]

55:00.833 --> 55:02.207
[both grunting]

55:02.208 --> 55:04.208
[music intensifies]

55:12.666 --> 55:14.666
[footsteps rumbling]

55:21.958 --> 55:23.250
[sensors whirring]

55:26.416 --> 55:28.000
Christ, my Lord and savior.

55:31.375 --> 55:32.458
[all yell]

55:34.666 --> 55:36.791
[all coughing]

55:37.500 --> 55:38.499
Oh my God!

55:38.500 --> 55:39.958
[intense music playing]

55:50.666 --> 55:52.500
- [44] Holy shit!
- [15] Oh my God!

56:00.000 --> 56:03.000
[gasping]

56:22.666 --> 56:23.833
[gasps]

56:37.416 --> 56:39.375
[gasping]

56:51.083 --> 56:52.333
Seven!

56:58.500 --> 57:00.500
[tense music playing]

57:11.000 --> 57:13.750
- [coughing]
- I got you! I got you.

57:18.708 --> 57:19.624
Watch out!

57:19.625 --> 57:21.375
[gasping]

57:25.083 --> 57:26.375
Falls!

57:27.000 --> 57:28.499
Falls!

57:28.500 --> 57:29.583
What?

57:30.583 --> 57:31.832
Falls!

57:31.833 --> 57:33.833
[intense music playing]

58:09.041 --> 58:11.041
[dramatic music playing]

58:27.708 --> 58:29.708
[music fades]

58:32.500 --> 58:34.499
[60, muffled] Eighty-one! Eighty-one!

58:34.500 --> 58:36.833
- I got you! Come on! I got you!
- [coughing]

58:37.708 --> 58:39.125
- [grunts]
- [gasping]

58:42.458 --> 58:44.708
He's alive! Seven is alive.

58:48.458 --> 58:49.750
[60] It's okay, Eighty-one.

58:51.083 --> 58:52.583
You can let go now.

58:53.291 --> 58:54.957
You saved him, bro.

58:54.958 --> 58:56.499
[44] Jesus, 60.

58:56.500 --> 58:59.249
How the hell did you get here?
We thought you were dead.

58:59.250 --> 59:02.207
[60] When that thing first attacked,
I got blown into the rapids.

59:02.208 --> 59:03.957
By the time I came up for air,

59:03.958 --> 59:07.416
I got swept so far downstream
I didn't know where I was.

59:08.000 --> 59:09.791
I thought everyone was dead.

59:11.500 --> 59:12.749
I started trekking west.

59:12.750 --> 59:14.832
That's when I saw y'all
come down the falls.

59:14.833 --> 59:16.749
You spot any sign of Cadre?

59:16.750 --> 59:19.624
No, but I did see the OPLAN
in Torres's office.

59:19.625 --> 59:22.957
All they had scheduled for us
was fireworks and booby traps.

59:22.958 --> 59:24.958
[unsettling music playing]

59:25.500 --> 59:26.791
You all right, little buddy?

59:27.958 --> 59:29.249
[60] Where were y'all headed?

59:29.250 --> 59:30.624
To the village.

59:30.625 --> 59:32.415
How far are we now?

59:32.416 --> 59:34.125
River's pushed us east.

59:34.791 --> 59:38.291
I had us about six klicks that way,
just beyond that ridge.

59:39.416 --> 59:40.999
Seems about right.

59:41.000 --> 59:42.665
[birds screeching]

59:42.666 --> 59:44.666
[ominous music playing]

59:47.000 --> 59:48.583
Let's get climbing!

01:00:02.041 --> 01:00:03.041
Think you can walk?

01:00:05.458 --> 01:00:06.333
Yeah.

01:00:06.833 --> 01:00:08.875
Well, keep moving,
or you're gonna die here.

01:00:11.000 --> 01:00:12.583
Help me with 7.

01:00:25.750 --> 01:00:27.750
[music fades]

01:00:32.250 --> 01:00:34.833
[suspenseful music playing]

01:00:50.208 --> 01:00:51.665
[music fades]

01:00:51.666 --> 01:00:53.666
[tense, pensive music playing]

01:00:56.250 --> 01:00:57.332
What is it?

01:00:57.333 --> 01:00:58.750
Got a trip.

01:01:03.125 --> 01:01:04.416
[15] They must be close.

01:01:04.916 --> 01:01:06.625
[81] It's connected to a flare.

01:01:07.333 --> 01:01:09.582
[60] <i>It's part of Cadre's
perimeter surveillance.</i>

01:01:09.583 --> 01:01:11.666
- [music fades]
- This'll be the first of three layers.

01:01:13.625 --> 01:01:15.625
[ominous music playing]

01:01:21.458 --> 01:01:22.583
[109] Cadre!

01:01:23.083 --> 01:01:24.458
Is anyone here?

01:01:26.291 --> 01:01:28.124
You sure this is the village?

01:01:28.125 --> 01:01:29.458
This was it.

01:01:30.625 --> 01:01:31.541
Put him down here.

01:01:40.750 --> 01:01:42.375
The hell happened here?

01:01:44.375 --> 01:01:45.500
The Machine.

01:01:46.083 --> 01:01:48.290
[109] But it's been behind us
the whole time.

01:01:48.291 --> 01:01:50.957
Look, the radio relay tower.

01:01:50.958 --> 01:01:52.707
No wonder long-range comms were out.

01:01:52.708 --> 01:01:54.125
Cadre!

01:01:56.833 --> 01:02:00.125
Don't tell me they fucking left us! Fuck!

01:02:01.833 --> 01:02:02.750
[44] No.

01:02:03.666 --> 01:02:05.083
They didn't leave us.

01:02:05.833 --> 01:02:08.207
[flies buzzing]

01:02:08.208 --> 01:02:10.250
[unsettling music playing]

01:02:21.666 --> 01:02:23.290
How high have we climbed?

01:02:23.291 --> 01:02:25.125
[44] About 6,500 feet.

01:02:25.916 --> 01:02:28.583
- [81] About eight klicks west?
- [44] About that.

01:02:30.333 --> 01:02:32.082
So it was on roughly a 20-degree angle,

01:02:32.083 --> 01:02:35.583
then hit this ridge before embedding down
in the riverbank where we demo'd it.

01:02:36.583 --> 01:02:37.833
So it came through…

01:02:40.208 --> 01:02:41.083
there.

01:02:45.083 --> 01:02:46.041
[15] Wait, hold on.

01:02:46.916 --> 01:02:50.707
You're telling me that this thing,
it smashed through a fucking mountain,

01:02:50.708 --> 01:02:52.958
and then just got up and walked around?

01:02:54.041 --> 01:02:57.290
Yo, we saw something on the TV
about an asteroid back at DFAC.

01:02:57.291 --> 01:02:59.291
I bet that's what that shit was.

01:03:00.125 --> 01:03:04.250
[15] Wait, you mean
it's from another planet?

01:03:06.250 --> 01:03:08.416
Well, it sure as shit ain't from this one.

01:03:09.041 --> 01:03:10.708
- [man groaning]
- [music fades]

01:03:11.375 --> 01:03:13.416
- Do y'all hear that?
- Hello!

01:03:14.875 --> 01:03:16.207
[man groans]

01:03:16.208 --> 01:03:17.291
Hello!

01:03:19.333 --> 01:03:20.500
[grunting]

01:03:21.958 --> 01:03:22.916
[60] It's all right.

01:03:24.416 --> 01:03:25.416
[109] Sergeant?

01:03:26.000 --> 01:03:27.540
[sergeant gasping]

01:03:27.541 --> 01:03:28.458
Sergeant.

01:03:30.208 --> 01:03:31.708
Sergeant.

01:03:32.916 --> 01:03:34.916
[somber music playing]

01:03:44.791 --> 01:03:45.791
Sergeant!

01:03:54.541 --> 01:03:56.333
Let's get that ASV on the ground.

01:03:56.916 --> 01:03:58.208
Everybody move.

01:03:59.208 --> 01:04:00.957
I think we might need a minute, man.

01:04:00.958 --> 01:04:02.375
We don't have a minute.

01:04:03.166 --> 01:04:05.250
We need a fucking minute, okay?!

01:04:06.875 --> 01:04:08.707
I don't know if you noticed it,

01:04:08.708 --> 01:04:11.416
the Cadre are dead
and half the fucking team are gone!

01:04:13.958 --> 01:04:15.458
So we need a minute.

01:04:17.000 --> 01:04:20.541
'Cause unlike you, we're actually human,
so we have to process shit.

01:04:21.333 --> 01:04:22.625
It's called emotion.

01:04:24.000 --> 01:04:25.582
I know that you can go on forever,

01:04:25.583 --> 01:04:28.040
and that you don't need sleep,
and you don't need us,

01:04:28.041 --> 01:04:30.791
but not everyone
is a Silver Star fucking war hero!

01:04:32.708 --> 01:04:34.208
The fuck did you call me?

01:04:34.916 --> 01:04:38.249
A hero. Everybody knows
81 carried his brother back to base--

01:04:38.250 --> 01:04:41.333
I am not a hero!
I never made it back to base!

01:04:43.291 --> 01:04:45.165
I woke up in a hospital,

01:04:45.166 --> 01:04:47.665
and he was already in a box
in the back of a plane.

01:04:47.666 --> 01:04:50.082
[poignant music playing]

01:04:50.083 --> 01:04:53.000
They told me I passed out
100 yards from the perimeter.

01:04:53.916 --> 01:04:55.915
He was still alive, do you understand?

01:04:55.916 --> 01:04:57.333
He died

01:04:58.583 --> 01:05:00.791
'cause I couldn't get him across the line.

01:05:01.666 --> 01:05:05.250
And they gave me a medal
for the worst day in my life.

01:05:33.000 --> 01:05:34.791
I know you're all hurting.

01:05:36.166 --> 01:05:37.166
I get it.

01:05:38.666 --> 01:05:40.458
But it's not about us anymore.

01:05:40.958 --> 01:05:42.874
[music turns dramatic]

01:05:42.875 --> 01:05:46.707
It's about firing up that Guardian,
getting 7 back to base,

01:05:46.708 --> 01:05:49.250
and warning everybody
that thing is coming.

01:05:59.250 --> 01:06:01.250
[music intensifies]

01:06:06.750 --> 01:06:08.083
[grunting]

01:06:09.500 --> 01:06:11.499
- How can I help?
- [81] Axle's jammed.

01:06:11.500 --> 01:06:12.999
We're gonna need to winch it.

01:06:13.000 --> 01:06:14.541
Get her engine started.

01:06:16.458 --> 01:06:18.458
[dramatic music continues]

01:06:26.666 --> 01:06:27.750
[engine sputtering]

01:06:28.875 --> 01:06:31.000
Come on,
you '90s-era surplus piece of shit!

01:06:33.833 --> 01:06:34.791
[109] It won't start!

01:06:35.791 --> 01:06:38.207
It's been on an angle,
so the fuel line's dry.

01:06:38.208 --> 01:06:40.541
- We need to re-prime the lines.
- [15] Re-prime the lines.

01:06:42.541 --> 01:06:44.666
- How'd you know that?
- [15] 91 Bravo.

01:06:45.583 --> 01:06:46.958
Wheel mechanic.

01:06:48.625 --> 01:06:49.458
Try now!

01:06:51.000 --> 01:06:51.915
[starter whirs]

01:06:51.916 --> 01:06:54.207
[engine rumbling]

01:06:54.208 --> 01:06:55.832
[laughing]

01:06:55.833 --> 01:06:57.291
That's it! We got it!

01:06:59.000 --> 01:07:01.040
[whoops] All the way, motherfuckers!

01:07:01.041 --> 01:07:04.207
One, two, three!

01:07:04.208 --> 01:07:06.208
[all grunting]

01:07:10.791 --> 01:07:12.000
[yells]

01:07:14.958 --> 01:07:15.833
[109] Come on!

01:07:16.458 --> 01:07:17.749
[yells]

01:07:17.750 --> 01:07:19.165
Pull! Pull! Pull!

01:07:19.166 --> 01:07:20.458
Come on!

01:07:22.958 --> 01:07:24.208
Yes! Yes! Yes!

01:07:27.125 --> 01:07:28.458
- [gasping]
- [music fades]

01:07:32.000 --> 01:07:33.540
[109] Yes. We did it!

01:07:33.541 --> 01:07:36.165
- [81] Nice work, Superman.
- [109] Let's get the hell out of here.

01:07:36.166 --> 01:07:37.707
[60] Second that, brother.

01:07:37.708 --> 01:07:39.583
Making the rest of us look bad.

01:07:41.208 --> 01:07:44.083
Holy shit. Eighty-one made a joke.

01:07:44.666 --> 01:07:47.457
Hey, dude bros.
Found Cadre's secret stash!

01:07:47.458 --> 01:07:48.790
[60 whoops]

01:07:48.791 --> 01:07:49.666
[109] Finally! Food.

01:07:50.291 --> 01:07:51.999
- [81] You still with us?
- [60] Forty-four.

01:07:52.000 --> 01:07:53.791
I ain't know I had a choice in that.

01:07:54.666 --> 01:07:56.082
Let's get you home.

01:07:56.083 --> 01:07:56.999
[15 grunts]

01:07:57.000 --> 01:07:58.583
[flares firing]

01:07:59.625 --> 01:08:02.165
[ominous music playing]

01:08:02.166 --> 01:08:03.457
Oh shit.

01:08:03.458 --> 01:08:05.874
- The Machine hit a tripwire!
- Check the perimeter!

01:08:05.875 --> 01:08:08.000
- Get that winch in!
- [44] Sixty, move!

01:08:08.916 --> 01:08:10.707
Get on that 50-cal, tanker!

01:08:10.708 --> 01:08:12.041
Yeah, I'm on it!

01:08:13.000 --> 01:08:14.000
[whirring]

01:08:14.583 --> 01:08:15.708
[44] No, no, no, no, no!

01:08:16.333 --> 01:08:17.875
- Come on.
- [engine rumbles]

01:08:19.250 --> 01:08:20.874
I'm pulling in the winch!

01:08:20.875 --> 01:08:22.000
[winch whirring]

01:08:23.708 --> 01:08:25.041
[15 grunting]

01:08:29.041 --> 01:08:30.874
Move! Move! Move! Move!

01:08:30.875 --> 01:08:32.415
[flares firing]

01:08:32.416 --> 01:08:35.249
[109] It's hit a second trip! Holy shit!

01:08:35.250 --> 01:08:36.832
We gotta go!

01:08:36.833 --> 01:08:38.124
We gotta move!

01:08:38.125 --> 01:08:40.665
Fuck! There's no ammo in this bitch.

01:08:40.666 --> 01:08:43.250
- I saw some back there.
- We don't have time. Fifteen!

01:08:45.458 --> 01:08:48.916
- Where the hell is he going?
- Trying to be a goddamn hero.

01:08:52.208 --> 01:08:53.500
[gasping]

01:08:54.416 --> 01:08:56.416
[tense music playing]

01:08:56.916 --> 01:08:58.458
[footsteps thudding]

01:09:04.000 --> 01:09:05.250
Shit.

01:09:05.833 --> 01:09:07.375
Fifteen, get your ass moving!

01:09:14.791 --> 01:09:16.541
Fifteen, run!

01:09:18.708 --> 01:09:20.833
[high-pitched ringing]

01:09:22.833 --> 01:09:24.915
[109] Drive! Drive!

01:09:24.916 --> 01:09:25.957
[60] Oh shit!

01:09:25.958 --> 01:09:27.958
[intense music playing]

01:09:29.083 --> 01:09:30.375
- [44 yells]
- [engine revving]

01:09:33.958 --> 01:09:35.250
- [60] Give me the ammo!
- [109] Go!

01:09:39.458 --> 01:09:40.791
Let's go, you piece of shit!

01:09:47.750 --> 01:09:50.458
- It's catching up!
- They're all bouncing right off it.

01:09:55.500 --> 01:09:56.874
[groans]

01:09:56.875 --> 01:09:58.166
We need more speed!

01:09:59.125 --> 01:10:00.457
[44] I'm redlining!

01:10:00.458 --> 01:10:01.791
Hold on! [yells]

01:10:04.708 --> 01:10:06.666
[60] Come on, come on, come on!

01:10:07.666 --> 01:10:08.875
[engine revs]

01:10:10.500 --> 01:10:12.166
[60] Some armor plating on this bitch!

01:10:14.583 --> 01:10:15.915
[gasps] Shit!

01:10:15.916 --> 01:10:16.833
[81] Put that out!

01:10:20.291 --> 01:10:22.249
[60] Our armor can't take any more!

01:10:22.250 --> 01:10:23.958
I think we're losing it!

01:10:27.583 --> 01:10:29.582
[60] Looks like it's falling back!

01:10:29.583 --> 01:10:31.583
[suspenseful music playing]

01:10:37.583 --> 01:10:38.750
Incoming!

01:10:44.041 --> 01:10:45.583
[yells]

01:10:47.000 --> 01:10:48.207
- [groans]
- [yelling]

01:10:48.208 --> 01:10:49.374
Hold on! Hold on!

01:10:49.375 --> 01:10:51.000
[intense music playing]

01:10:55.750 --> 01:10:58.291
- Hold it fucking steady!
- I'm trying!

01:11:20.666 --> 01:11:21.541
[grunting]

01:11:24.791 --> 01:11:26.416
Hold on!

01:11:30.208 --> 01:11:31.457
[grunting and yelling]

01:11:31.458 --> 01:11:32.500
Fuck.

01:11:33.666 --> 01:11:35.000
[grunting]

01:11:39.958 --> 01:11:40.958
[44 yells]

01:11:46.916 --> 01:11:49.124
[gasping]

01:11:49.125 --> 01:11:52.124
[music crescendos, then fades]

01:11:52.125 --> 01:11:54.915
Tell me we lost it, guys.
This transmission's smoked.

01:11:54.916 --> 01:11:56.250
Sixty, you got eyes?

01:11:56.916 --> 01:11:57.750
I can't see it.

01:12:00.041 --> 01:12:01.708
I think we outran it.

01:12:11.166 --> 01:12:13.166
[ominous music playing]

01:12:19.708 --> 01:12:21.750
- Shit!
- [alert blaring]

01:12:27.833 --> 01:12:29.625
[all yelling]

01:12:30.958 --> 01:12:32.958
[intense music playing]

01:12:36.500 --> 01:12:37.999
- It's pissed!
- Fight back!

01:12:38.000 --> 01:12:39.375
[60] Yo, I'm trying!

01:12:39.875 --> 01:12:41.207
Oh God.

01:12:41.208 --> 01:12:44.749
- It's gotta have a weakness, right?
- [44] We're pissing hydraulic fluid!

01:12:44.750 --> 01:12:46.582
Faster! Faster! Come on!

01:12:46.583 --> 01:12:47.958
Hit it between the plates!

01:12:53.750 --> 01:12:55.750
[intense music continues]

01:13:06.125 --> 01:13:08.249
Hold her steady!

01:13:08.250 --> 01:13:09.583
I'm working on it!

01:13:13.541 --> 01:13:15.541
[screaming]

01:13:18.666 --> 01:13:21.250
Oh God! [wailing]

01:13:45.208 --> 01:13:47.041
This thing is falling apart!

01:14:00.916 --> 01:14:03.166
[81 grunting]

01:14:04.833 --> 01:14:05.958
No!

01:14:15.583 --> 01:14:16.583
Stop!

01:14:17.333 --> 01:14:18.833
Hey, stop!

01:14:29.291 --> 01:14:31.291
[music fades]

01:14:33.166 --> 01:14:35.166
[dramatic, poignant music playing]

01:14:58.583 --> 01:15:00.249
[heart beat thudding]

01:15:00.250 --> 01:15:02.875
[younger brother] <i>Don't fucking quit.</i>

01:15:03.375 --> 01:15:05.457
[gasping]

01:15:05.458 --> 01:15:07.958
[thunder rumbling]

01:15:11.000 --> 01:15:13.000
[haunting music playing]

01:16:06.916 --> 01:16:08.916
[thunder rumbles]

01:16:14.750 --> 01:16:16.500
[grunting]

01:16:25.625 --> 01:16:26.625
What?

01:16:27.750 --> 01:16:29.125
Where's the rest of it?

01:16:34.500 --> 01:16:36.000
[warbling]

01:16:41.458 --> 01:16:42.415
[grunts]

01:16:42.416 --> 01:16:44.416
[music turns ominous]

01:17:01.208 --> 01:17:03.125
Who the hell are you talking to?

01:17:27.125 --> 01:17:28.249
Hey.

01:17:28.250 --> 01:17:29.375
Hey, 7.

01:17:30.000 --> 01:17:31.749
Hey, you with me?

01:17:31.750 --> 01:17:32.916
[ammunition exploding]

01:17:44.416 --> 01:17:46.416
[ominous music continues]

01:17:52.000 --> 01:17:56.583
[sensor whirring]

01:18:07.166 --> 01:18:09.540
[music crescendos, then fades]

01:18:09.541 --> 01:18:11.541
[thunder rumbles]

01:18:12.708 --> 01:18:14.708
[81 grunting]

01:18:20.625 --> 01:18:22.625
[dramatic music playing]

01:18:31.000 --> 01:18:33.000
[grunting]

01:18:49.875 --> 01:18:50.750
[yells]

01:18:52.250 --> 01:18:53.583
[yells]

01:18:59.166 --> 01:19:00.291
Fuck!

01:19:03.166 --> 01:19:04.208
Fuck!

01:19:05.500 --> 01:19:07.250
Fuck!

01:19:13.333 --> 01:19:14.666
[yelling]

01:19:16.708 --> 01:19:17.791
[grunts]

01:19:18.708 --> 01:19:20.416
[yelling]

01:19:21.958 --> 01:19:22.791
[groans]

01:19:23.500 --> 01:19:26.332
Fuck! Fuck! You fucked me!

01:19:26.333 --> 01:19:28.541
- Fuck!
- [watch beeping]

01:19:32.666 --> 01:19:35.166
You suck, you fucking piece of shit.

01:19:58.208 --> 01:20:00.666
[sobs softly]

01:20:01.750 --> 01:20:03.291
I knew who you were…

01:20:05.500 --> 01:20:07.625
the moment I saw you on that bus.

01:20:08.375 --> 01:20:11.707
I went through Air Assault
with a loudmouth private.

01:20:11.708 --> 01:20:13.708
[poignant music playing]

01:20:14.291 --> 01:20:16.625
Got this dumb tattoo on his arm.

01:20:19.791 --> 01:20:21.250
"D.F.Q."

01:20:27.458 --> 01:20:29.041
You knew my brother?

01:20:31.666 --> 01:20:34.416
He wouldn't shut up
about becoming a Ranger with you.

01:20:37.916 --> 01:20:40.416
I was on furlough when I heard he passed.

01:20:43.541 --> 01:20:45.000
Why didn't you tell me?

01:20:47.000 --> 01:20:48.083
I tried.

01:20:55.125 --> 01:20:56.583
I just thought, uh…

01:21:02.208 --> 01:21:04.916
if I could get across
that finish line for him…

01:21:08.041 --> 01:21:09.875
maybe it could help me sleep.

01:21:13.458 --> 01:21:15.208
You think you failed your brother?

01:21:17.875 --> 01:21:19.375
I failed everybody.

01:21:20.958 --> 01:21:22.708
But you never gave up.

01:21:24.416 --> 01:21:26.000
That's not failure.

01:21:28.458 --> 01:21:29.833
That's a Ranger.

01:21:39.291 --> 01:21:41.291
[sensor whirring]

01:21:43.583 --> 01:21:45.375
[music turns ominous]

01:21:51.833 --> 01:21:53.749
[81] That thing doesn't quit either.

01:21:53.750 --> 01:21:56.124
How the fuck
are we supposed to stop this thing?

01:21:56.125 --> 01:21:57.832
What would your brother do?

01:21:57.833 --> 01:21:59.791
[thunder rumbles]

01:22:01.583 --> 01:22:03.583
Probably fill it with Stop Leak.

01:22:04.083 --> 01:22:06.083
[both laughing]

01:22:21.583 --> 01:22:22.583
Wait.

01:22:23.208 --> 01:22:26.249
- It's venting.
- What does that mean?

01:22:26.250 --> 01:22:28.250
[music turns dramatic]

01:22:31.833 --> 01:22:33.083
I got an idea.

01:22:33.666 --> 01:22:35.999
[both grunting]

01:22:36.000 --> 01:22:38.875
- Can you wait here for me?
- Yeah. I can wait.

01:22:39.375 --> 01:22:41.375
[thunder crashes]

01:22:43.458 --> 01:22:45.458
[81 grunting]

01:23:06.708 --> 01:23:08.708
[dramatic music playing]

01:23:41.166 --> 01:23:42.291
[beeping]

01:23:52.166 --> 01:23:53.499
Where are the rocks?

01:23:53.500 --> 01:23:55.457
Cone crusher.

01:23:55.458 --> 01:23:57.791
This is… How the fuck do you turn this on?

01:24:14.333 --> 01:24:16.375
Thermodynamics, motherfucker.

01:24:17.333 --> 01:24:19.333
[footsteps thudding]

01:24:40.041 --> 01:24:41.750
[tense music playing]

01:25:11.583 --> 01:25:12.791
[music fades]

01:25:19.916 --> 01:25:21.916
[thunder rumbling]

01:25:22.958 --> 01:25:24.958
[dark music playing]

01:26:01.875 --> 01:26:03.875
[explosives beeping]

01:26:22.708 --> 01:26:24.166
Come on!

01:26:29.375 --> 01:26:30.208
[grunts]

01:26:31.541 --> 01:26:32.625
[grunts]

01:26:35.083 --> 01:26:36.374
You want a piece of me?

01:26:36.375 --> 01:26:38.375
[intense music playing]

01:27:09.125 --> 01:27:10.750
No! [grunts]

01:27:15.083 --> 01:27:16.082
[yells]

01:27:16.083 --> 01:27:17.958
No. No!

01:27:19.833 --> 01:27:20.750
Come on!

01:27:21.958 --> 01:27:22.833
No, no, no.

01:27:24.166 --> 01:27:25.458
[yells]

01:27:31.708 --> 01:27:32.958
[yells]

01:27:33.916 --> 01:27:35.916
[intense music continues]

01:27:43.125 --> 01:27:44.125
Breathe, you fucker!

01:27:46.583 --> 01:27:48.000
Stop Leak, bitch.

01:28:04.916 --> 01:28:06.374
[alarms blaring]

01:28:06.375 --> 01:28:07.208
Oh…

01:28:10.666 --> 01:28:11.500
[yells]

01:28:17.958 --> 01:28:19.333
Yes!

01:28:24.958 --> 01:28:26.166
Stay with me!

01:28:42.958 --> 01:28:44.249
[yells]

01:28:44.250 --> 01:28:45.749
[grunts]

01:28:45.750 --> 01:28:47.750
[intense music continues]

01:29:01.708 --> 01:29:02.625
[gasps]

01:29:16.791 --> 01:29:18.791
[music fades]

01:29:24.750 --> 01:29:25.916
[exhales]

01:29:31.916 --> 01:29:33.833
[ominous music playing]

01:29:37.750 --> 01:29:39.291
You gotta be shitting me.

01:29:40.708 --> 01:29:42.708
[music turns tense]

01:29:45.583 --> 01:29:47.250
[whirring]

01:30:01.875 --> 01:30:03.875
[music fades]

01:30:08.500 --> 01:30:10.500
[dramatic music playing]

01:30:22.416 --> 01:30:24.416
[breathing heavily]

01:30:30.125 --> 01:30:32.500
[helicopters whirring]

01:30:44.291 --> 01:30:46.291
[dramatic music continues]

01:30:54.375 --> 01:30:55.957
[indistinct radio chatter]

01:30:55.958 --> 01:30:57.750
[speaks indistinctly]

01:31:01.958 --> 01:31:03.958
[dramatic music intensifies]

01:31:39.583 --> 01:31:40.915
[grunting]

01:31:40.916 --> 01:31:42.166
[groaning]

01:31:51.000 --> 01:31:52.125
All the way.

01:31:54.375 --> 01:31:55.791
All the way, brother.

01:31:57.708 --> 01:31:59.665
[soldier 1] Hey, there's more
injured over here!

01:31:59.666 --> 01:32:00.916
[soldier 2] Let's go!

01:32:04.041 --> 01:32:05.958
Lift him up! Let's go!

01:32:08.458 --> 01:32:10.458
[dramatic music continues]

01:32:27.750 --> 01:32:29.000
[Sergeant Major] Candidate.

01:32:31.125 --> 01:32:32.666
Are you all that's left?

01:32:35.041 --> 01:32:36.750
[somber music playing]

01:32:38.791 --> 01:32:41.458
I'm sorry we couldn't reach you sooner.

01:32:42.458 --> 01:32:46.458
We only just secured this base.
We lost half the battalion.

01:32:49.291 --> 01:32:50.500
How many are there?

01:32:51.250 --> 01:32:52.457
They're everywhere.

01:32:52.458 --> 01:32:55.041
We've neutralized the first wave.

01:32:55.750 --> 01:32:58.916
But we're preparing for a global invasion.

01:33:00.583 --> 01:33:04.249
[man on TV] <i>36 hours ago,
what NASA believed to be an asteroid</i>

01:33:04.250 --> 01:33:08.832
<i>split into countless pods
that impacted sites across the globe.</i>

01:33:08.833 --> 01:33:12.540
<i>These pods transformed
into deadly machines…</i>

01:33:12.541 --> 01:33:13.915
Pupils reactive and equal.

01:33:13.916 --> 01:33:16.540
<i>…attacking cities, civilians,
and defense networks alike.</i>

01:33:16.541 --> 01:33:20.207
<i>But just as the world's militaries
managed to contain the threat,</i>

01:33:20.208 --> 01:33:22.749
<i>interstellar imaging
confirms our worst fear.</i>

01:33:22.750 --> 01:33:23.665
[medic] Your fingers.

01:33:23.666 --> 01:33:26.582
<i>Tens of thousands more are on their way.</i>

01:33:26.583 --> 01:33:29.915
<i>A coordinated global response
is now being launched,</i>

01:33:29.916 --> 01:33:34.332
<i>with allied forces mobilizing
across air, land, and sea.</i>

01:33:34.333 --> 01:33:38.457
<i>We don't know what they want.
We don't know why they're here.</i>

01:33:38.458 --> 01:33:40.165
<i>But every nation on Earth…</i>

01:33:40.166 --> 01:33:41.082
[soldier] Corporal.

01:33:41.083 --> 01:33:42.499
<i>…is now preparing for war.</i>

01:33:42.500 --> 01:33:43.916
We're ready to see you now.

01:33:45.375 --> 01:33:46.832
[Torres] <i>A global military alliance</i>

01:33:46.833 --> 01:33:48.874
<i>is about to launch
our first counteroffensive.</i>

01:33:48.875 --> 01:33:51.999
Only problem is we've thrown
everything we have at these things.

01:33:52.000 --> 01:33:53.707
These machines don't die easy.

01:33:53.708 --> 01:33:55.707
[Sergeant Major] What we need to know is,

01:33:55.708 --> 01:33:59.250
how the hell did you take one down
without any weapons?

01:34:01.041 --> 01:34:03.041
Like you said, Sergeant Major.

01:34:04.083 --> 01:34:06.125
Every machine has its limits.

01:34:07.833 --> 01:34:09.708
The primary venting port here.

01:34:10.708 --> 01:34:12.416
Like a radiator in a Humvee.

01:34:13.208 --> 01:34:15.582
If you jam it hard enough,
the whole system chokes.

01:34:15.583 --> 01:34:17.999
[pensive music playing]

01:34:18.000 --> 01:34:20.040
Get CENTCOM on the line.

01:34:20.041 --> 01:34:22.374
Torres, you heard the man.
Let's saddle up!

01:34:22.375 --> 01:34:23.416
[Torres] I'm on it.

01:34:25.791 --> 01:34:28.291
Your intel's gonna save a lot of lives.

01:34:29.833 --> 01:34:31.833
You were right, Sergeant Major.

01:34:33.583 --> 01:34:34.708
I wasn't ready.

01:34:35.375 --> 01:34:37.708
[dramatic, poignant music playing]

01:34:42.916 --> 01:34:44.083
You are now.

01:34:47.208 --> 01:34:48.833
Welcome to the Regiment.

01:34:53.208 --> 01:34:55.125
Your brother'd be proud.

01:34:57.916 --> 01:35:00.541
[Torres] Rangers, kit up!
We're moving out! Let's go!

01:35:03.541 --> 01:35:07.041
You know, they're all talking
about what you did out there.

01:35:07.875 --> 01:35:13.000
If you got it in you, son,
I'm sure they'd appreciate a few words.

01:35:15.458 --> 01:35:17.165
[Torres] Rangers have been tasked

01:35:17.166 --> 01:35:19.540
as the spearhead
of Operation Global Shield.

01:35:19.541 --> 01:35:24.540
Joining a full-scale military mobilization
across air, land, and sea.

01:35:24.541 --> 01:35:29.166
Your Black Hawks escorted by F-35 fighters
will drop you on the city outskirts.

01:35:29.791 --> 01:35:34.666
Your mission is to clear civilians
and make way for heavy ordnance.

01:35:35.500 --> 01:35:38.500
United States military's
never faced an enemy like this.

01:35:39.416 --> 01:35:41.165
But we're gonna rise to the occasion.

01:35:41.166 --> 01:35:43.625
[determined music playing]

01:35:57.125 --> 01:35:59.541
I know how some of you are feeling.

01:36:01.083 --> 01:36:02.000
Hurt.

01:36:03.833 --> 01:36:04.875
Tired.

01:36:06.666 --> 01:36:08.083
Maybe even scared.

01:36:09.875 --> 01:36:12.500
But we are Rangers.

01:36:13.666 --> 01:36:14.791
We fight for each other.

01:36:16.708 --> 01:36:19.416
And we fight for those
who never made it home.

01:36:20.750 --> 01:36:22.208
We don't back down.

01:36:23.791 --> 01:36:25.208
We don't break.

01:36:26.416 --> 01:36:29.665
And we sure as hell don't fucking quit.

01:36:29.666 --> 01:36:31.290
[in unison] Hell yeah!

01:36:31.291 --> 01:36:33.040
Rangers lead the way!

01:36:33.041 --> 01:36:34.832
[in unison] All the way!

01:36:34.833 --> 01:36:36.416
[music intensifies]

01:37:07.458 --> 01:37:12.165
[soldier] <i>All CA elements, check in.
This is Chalk Leader Fox 1, spinning up.</i>

01:37:12.166 --> 01:37:13.624
[pilot 1] <i>Fox 2, up and ready.</i>

01:37:13.625 --> 01:37:15.416
[pilot 2] <i>Fox 3, standing by.</i>

01:37:16.958 --> 01:37:19.666
[dramatic music playing]

01:37:28.708 --> 01:37:31.832
[officer on comm] <i>Black Hawk squadron,
you are green across the board.</i>

01:37:31.833 --> 01:37:33.832
<i>F-35s have your escort.</i>

01:37:33.833 --> 01:37:36.374
<i>Operation Global Shield is live.</i>

01:37:36.375 --> 01:37:38.208
<i>Godspeed, Rangers.</i>

01:37:39.791 --> 01:37:43.374
Chalk Leader Fox 1
with seven packs on board.

01:37:43.375 --> 01:37:46.750
McQueen, Lieberman, Young, Janus, Cook.

01:37:50.458 --> 01:37:53.208
Hey! Anybody catch his name?

01:38:01.291 --> 01:38:04.291
[dramatic music continues]

01:39:38.208 --> 01:39:39.290
[music fades]

01:39:39.291 --> 01:39:41.291
[intense music playing]

01:41:08.291 --> 01:41:10.291
[music turns ominous]

01:42:03.916 --> 01:42:05.916
[music turns dramatic]

01:43:06.791 --> 01:43:08.791
[music turns poignant]

01:44:53.708 --> 01:44:55.708
[music turns dramatic]

01:46:29.166 --> 01:46:31.166
[music fades]
